This paper deals with the fundamental performance limits of the interference channel in the presence of an external eavesdropper, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the optimization of wireless networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the Gaussian case, which is related to signal processing (cs.MM).
